HEADWORD: Demolition
<hw>Dem`o*li"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>demolitio</ets>, fr. <ets>demoliri</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧molition</ets>. See <er>Demolish</er>.]</ety> <def>The act
of overthrowing, pulling down, or destroying a pile or structure;
destruction by violence; utter overthrow; -- opposed to
<xex>construction</xex>; <as>as, the <ex>demolition</ex> of a house, of
military works, of a town, or of hopes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demolitionist</ent>⟦br⟧
